Class OffsiteContext

Direct Known Subclasses:
InternalPartnerContext
public class OffsiteContext
extends SecurityContext

Security context for off-site apps. Provides a series of calls that performs an OAuth login workflow. After you have obtained the access token for the user, you can create a MySpace API wrapper object (e.g., RestV1 or PortableContacts) and start making calls to fetch and store data.

Method Detail

getRequestToken

public OAuthToken getRequestToken(java.lang.String callbackURL)
Returns the request token. After this, allow the user to authenticate himself by redirecting to the URL found by calling getAuthorizationURL(com.myspace.myspaceid.oauth.OAuthToken).

Parameters:
callbackURL - The callback URL that MySpace redirects the user to after she authenticates successfully.
Returns:
A request token.

getAuthorizationURL

public java.lang.String getAuthorizationURL(OAuthToken requestToken)
Returns the authorization URL that you should redirect to for the user to authenticate. After successful authentication, the user's browser is redirected back to the callback URL. The callback URL receives an oauth_token parameter that you need to pick up and then call getAccessToken().

Parameters:
requestToken - The request token obtained by calling getRequestToken(java.lang.String).
Returns:
the authorization URL that you should redirect to for the user to authenticate.

getAccessToken

public OAuthToken getAccessToken()
Returns the access token for the user. The side effect of this call is to set the access token in this OffsiteContext object. Make sure you call this using the constructor that sets the (authorized) request token. so that you can now use it to create a RestV1 (or other REST wrapper object) to start fetching user data.

Returns:
An access token; you can now start getting user data with this access token.

getAccessToken

public OAuthToken getAccessToken(java.lang.String oauthVerifier)
Returns the access token for the user. The side effect of this call is to set the access token in this OffsiteContext object. Make sure you call this using the constructor that sets the (authorized) request token. so that you can now use it to create a RestV1 (or other REST wrapper object) to start fetching user data.

Parameters:
oauthVerifier - oauth_verifier parameter returned in the callback for OAuth 1.0a workflow
Returns:
An access token; you can now start getting user data with this access token.
